# Domain Purity

## Zero framework dependencies

- ❌ `using Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore` — forbidden.
- ❌ `using Microsoft.AspNetCore.*` — forbidden.
- ❌ `using MediatR` — forbidden in Domain (events use a local `IDomainEvent` marker).
- ❌ `using AutoMapper` / `using Mapster` — forbidden.
- ✅ `NetTopologySuite.Geometries` — allowed (it's a math library, not infra).

## Entity contract

```csharp
public sealed class Report : AuditableEntity, IAggregateRoot
{
    private readonly List<IDomainEvent> _events = [];
    private readonly List<ReportMedia> _media = [];

    public Guid Id { get; private set; }
    public ReportStatus Status { get; private set; }     // private setter — only domain methods change state
    public Point Location { get; private set; }
    public IReadOnlyList<ReportMedia> Media => _media.AsReadOnly();
    public IReadOnlyList<IDomainEvent> DomainEvents => _events.AsReadOnly();

    private Report() { }   // EF needs this; keep private

    public static Report Create(PollutionType type, Point location, Guid userId)
    {
        // BR-REP-013: initial state is Submitted
        var report = new Report { Id = Guid.NewGuid(), Status = ReportStatus.Submitted, /*...*/ };
        report._events.Add(new ReportSubmittedEvent(report.Id, userId));
        return report;
    }
}
```

## State transitions ARE domain methods

```csharp
// ✅ State machine guarded by domain
public void Verify(Guid officerId)
{
    // BR-REP-020: only Submitted → Verified is valid
    if (Status != ReportStatus.Submitted)
        throw new DomainException("Invalid transition: Verify requires Submitted state");

    Status = ReportStatus.Verified;
    VerifiedBy = officerId;
    VerifiedAt = DateTime.UtcNow;
    _events.Add(new ReportVerifiedEvent(Id, officerId));
}

// ❌ NEVER do this
public ReportStatus Status { get; set; }   // public setter bypasses state machine
```

## State machine (BR-REP-020, BR-REP-021)

```
                ┌─► Rejected   (Officer, reason ≥ 20 chars)
Submitted ─────┼─► Verified ──► InProgress ──► Resolved ──┬─► Closed (Citizen confirm OR auto 7d)
                └─► Duplicate  (Officer/AI)               └─► InProgress (re-open, max 2 times)
```

Every transition method:
1. Guards state precondition.
2. Mutates state via private setters.
3. Sets audit fields.
4. Adds the corresponding `DomainEvent` to `_events`.

## Value objects

```csharp
public readonly record struct GeoLocation(double Latitude, double Longitude)
{
    public static GeoLocation Create(double lat, double lng)
    {
        // BR-REP-003: Vietnam bounds
        if (lat is < 8.0 or > 24.0) throw new DomainException("Latitude out of Vietnam range");
        if (lng is < 102.0 or > 110.0) throw new DomainException("Longitude out of Vietnam range");
        return new GeoLocation(lat, lng);
    }
}
```

## Domain events

`record XxxEvent(...) : IDomainEvent` — handled by Application via outbox dispatcher.
